If your machine is capable, try switching the RED nodes. using the VAE Decode node will assist in removing color glitching. 
Simply connect the latent output from the KSampler to the samples input of the VAE decode node. 
Then, connect the image output from the VAE Decode node to the ImagePass node

Overexposure, static, blurred details, subtitles, paintings, pictures, still, overall gray, worst quality, low quality, JPEG compression residue, ugly, mutilated, redundant fingers, poorly painted hands, poorly painted faces, deformed, disfigured, deformed limbs, fused fingers, cluttered background, three legs, a lot of people in the background, upside down

SageAttention disabled by default, if you're systems supports that enable it. 
If you enabled it and wish to disable, you have to change sage_attention in the node to disabled and run your workflow again in order for it to disable
These nodes are for removing the first 6 frames from the image, these are junk frames that hurt the natural flow of the video ↓
Recommended size for initial frame generation:

In this group you can find the first frame of every reference video. 
You can use these images to create a starting frame that will make the video look more realistic.

I recommend using the LSDIR upscaler, get it here: 
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-LSDIR
